   "source": [
    "df = contracts.join(customers, how='inner') \n",
    "df['deposit'] = df['deposit'].str.replace('$', '')\n",
    "df['deposit'] = df['deposit'].str.replace(',', '')\n",
    "\n",
    "df['monthly_amt'] = df['monthly_amt'].str.replace('$', '')\n",
    "df['monthly_amt'] = df['monthly_amt'].str.replace(',', '')\n",
    "df[[\"deposit\", \"monthly_amt\"]] = df[[\"deposit\", \"monthly_amt\"]].apply(pd.to_numeric)\n",
    "df[\"total_monthlyamt\"] = df[\"contract_term\"] * df[\"monthly_amt\"]\n",
    "df[\"total_sales\"] = df[\"total_monthlyamt\"] + df[\"deposit\"]\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "new_df= pd.DataFrame(df, columns = ['total_sales', 'company'])\n",
    "new_df['total_sales']=new_df['total_sales'].astype(int)\n",
    "tot_df = new_df.groupby('company')['total_sales'].sum().reset_index()\n",
    "companies_df = tot_df.nlargest(10, ['total_sales'])\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = sns.barplot(x=\"company\", y=\"total_sales\", data=companies_df)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=40, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='Companies', ylabel='Total Sales (Millions US$)')\n",
    "companies_df"
   ]

    "### Top Selling Companies\n",
    "\n",
    "This graph shows the 10 best selling companies in the dataset. This is important to know because we can see which companies are primarily driving sales.
